  "analysis": "The terminal output is showing parts of main but the commands are producing too much output and getting truncated. I need a more efficient approach: use objdump with intel syntax and pipe through grep for immediate values and call patterns, or use a disassembler script to extract constants and structure more compactly.",
  "plan": "I will use objdump with intel syntax to save to a file, then write a Python script to parse the disassembly and extract all instructions with immediate values and RIP-relative loads, focusing on key functions. This will give a compact view of the algorithm.",
